    <p>Goli pioneered the ACV gummy category and remains the market leader by a wide margin. What separates the ACV + Weight formula from their original ACV gummy is the addition of Morosil — a patented blood orange extract rich in anthocyanins and hydroxycinnamic acids. A 2015 randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled trial published in <em>International Journal of Food Sciences and Nutrition</em> found that 400mg of Morosil daily for 12 weeks significantly reduced BMI, hip circumference, and waist circumference compared to placebo in overweight but otherwise healthy adults.</p>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <span class="tip-box-ico">&#128161;</span>
      <p><strong>Why Morosil matters:</strong> Unlike generic citrus extracts, Morosil is a standardized, patented ingredient with its own clinical trial data. The anthocyanin profile in blood oranges from Sicily activates AMPK (AMP-activated protein kinase) — the same metabolic pathway targeted by the diabetes drug metformin. This is not a theoretical mechanism; it has been demonstrated in the published human trial at the exact 400mg dose used in Goli's formula.</p>
    </div>

