    <!-- INGREDIENT BOX -->
    <div class="ing-box">
      <h4>Weight Loss Gummy Ingredients: Mechanisms, Doses, and Evidence Levels</h4>
      <p>Not every ingredient marketed for weight loss has clinical support. Here is what the research actually says about the most common active compounds found in weight management gummies.</p>

      <div class="vs-strip">
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Apple Cider Vinegar (Acetic Acid)</strong>
          <p>Clinical dose: 750-1500mg acetic acid daily (15-30mL liquid ACV). Mechanism: modulates appetite, slows gastric emptying, improves insulin sensitivity. Evidence level: moderate — multiple RCTs show modest body weight reduction when combined with calorie restriction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Green Tea Extract (EGCG)</strong>
          <p>Clinical dose: 250-500mg EGCG daily. Mechanism: increases thermogenesis and fat oxidation via norepinephrine pathway inhibition. Evidence level: strong — confirmed in meta-analyses of 11+ studies. Effect: 80-100 extra calories burned per day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Chromium Picolinate</strong>
          <p>Clinical dose: 200-1000mcg daily. Mechanism: enhances insulin receptor signaling and glucose transporter activity. Evidence level: moderate — meta-analysis of 21 RCTs shows significant BMI and body weight reductions, particularly in overweight populations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vs-item">
          <strong>Green Coffee Bean Extract</strong>
          <p>Clinical dose: 200-400mg daily. Mechanism: chlorogenic acid inhibits glucose-6-phosphatase, reducing hepatic glucose output and promoting fat utilization. Evidence level: moderate — limited independent studies, most research is brand-funded.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <span class="tip-box-ico">&#128138;</span>
        <p><strong>Dose reality check:</strong> The single biggest limitation of weight loss gummies is fitting clinically effective doses into a palatable format. A gummy weighing 3-5 grams simply cannot contain 500mg of EGCG, 1000mg of ACV, and meaningful amounts of CLA without becoming unpalatably large. Always check the actual milligram content per serving against the clinical doses listed above.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="warn-box">
        <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
        <p><strong>No supplement replaces a calorie deficit:</strong> The most effective weight loss gummy in this guide produces a metabolic advantage equivalent to approximately 100 calories per day. To lose one pound of fat, you need a cumulative deficit of approximately 3,500 calories. Supplements are a tool — not a strategy. Combine them with nutrition counseling, progressive exercise, adequate sleep (7-9 hours), and stress management for meaningful, sustainable results.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

